	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64251148"><p>The fingerprint is described as cryptographically signed, which is, one presumes, far more difficult to fake.</p><p>You turn that fingerprint into a number (or even just an image), you sign it with the manufacturer's private key, and the scanner at the warehouse confirms it with their public key.</p><p>No idea how well it will work, or how well it will be implemented, but the concept is sound enough.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64251148">

